# 🎭 Deepfake Detection System

A multi-modal deepfake detection pipeline using deep learning for visual, temporal, and audio analysis of manipulated media.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10-blue?style=flat&logo=python)
![PyTorch](https://img.shields.io/badge/PyTorch-2.x-red?style=flat&logo=pytorch)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green?style=flat)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Active-brightgreen?style=flat)

---

## 📌 Overview

This project implements a **7-stage deepfake detection pipeline** that combines visual, spatiotemporal, and audio analysis to identify AI-generated or manipulated media. The system is designed to handle both image-based and video-based deepfakes with explainable AI output using Grad-CAM.

---

## 🧠 Architecture

```
Input Media
    │
    ▼
[Stage 1] Face Detection        →  MTCNN
    │
    ▼
[Stage 2] Visual Analysis       →  XceptionNet / EfficientNet (CNN)
    │
    ▼
[Stage 3] Temporal Analysis     →  LSTM (frame-level consistency)
    │
    ▼
[Stage 4] Audio Analysis        →  RawNet2
    │
    ▼
[Stage 5] Multimodal Fusion     →  Cross-modal verification
    │
    ▼
[Stage 6] Explainability        →  Grad-CAM heatmap generation
    │
    ▼
[Stage 7] Output                →  Streamlit dashboard (Real / Fake + confidence)
```

---

## ✨ Features

- **Face Detection** — MTCNN-based face extraction from video frames
- **Visual Deepfake Detection** — XceptionNet and EfficientNet for spatial artifact detection
- **Temporal Consistency Check** — LSTM to detect frame-level inconsistencies over time
- **Audio Deepfake Detection** — RawNet2 for voice synthesis detection
- **Explainability** — Grad-CAM heatmaps showing *why* a video is flagged as fake
- **Interactive UI** — Streamlit-based dashboard for real-time analysis
- **Multi-approach coverage** — GAN, VAE, and Diffusion-based deepfake detection

---

