## 📁 Project Structure

```
Deepfake-Detection/
├── data/
│   ├── raw/                  # Input videos/images
│   └── processed/            # Preprocessed face crops
├── models/
│   ├── visual/               # XceptionNet, EfficientNet weights
│   ├── temporal/             # LSTM model
│   └── audio/                # RawNet2 model
├── pipeline/
│   ├── face_detection.py     # MTCNN face extraction
│   ├── visual_analysis.py    # CNN-based detection
│   ├── temporal_analysis.py  # LSTM consistency check
│   ├── audio_analysis.py     # RawNet2 audio detection
│   └── fusion.py             # Multimodal fusion
├── explainability/
│   └── gradcam.py            # Grad-CAM heatmaps
├── app.py                    # Streamlit dashboard
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.10+
- CUDA-compatible GPU (tested on RTX 2050, 8GB RAM)
- Git

### Install Dependencies

```bash
git clone https://github.com/sahilborhade77/Deepfake-Detection.git
cd Deepfake-Detection
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Run the App

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 🚀 Usage

1. Launch the Streamlit dashboard
2. Upload a video or image file
3. Click **Analyze**
4. View the prediction (Real / Fake), confidence score, and Grad-CAM heatmap

---

## 📊 Detection Approaches Covered

| Deepfake Type | Detection Method |
|---|---|
| GAN-based (FaceSwap, DeepFaceLab) | XceptionNet spatial artifact detection |
| VAE-based | EfficientNet feature analysis |
| Diffusion-based | Temporal + frequency analysis |
| Voice cloning | RawNet2 audio model |
| Lip-sync fakes | Cross-modal audio-visual fusion |

---

## 🔍 Explainability — Grad-CAM

The system generates **Grad-CAM heatmaps** that highlight which facial regions contributed most to the fake classification — making the model's decision transparent and interpretable.

---

## 📚 Literature Survey

This project is backed by a comprehensive literature survey covering:
- GAN/VAE/Diffusion-based generation techniques
- CNN and Vision Transformer (ViT) detection approaches
- Spatiotemporal and multimodal detection methods
- Audio deepfake detection

